cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the analysis of multiple sensors capturing a complex system or a physical phenomenon of interest. This involves the extraction of latent variables from the sensor data. The paper proposes an algorithm for this purpose and demonstrates its effectiveness on three different applications. The paper's focus on machine learning and data analysis suggests that it is most likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of multimodal sensors and the analysis of complex systems suggest that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories. The theoretical analysis of the proposed algorithm suggests that it could belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Finally, the use of the algorithm for fetal ECG extraction suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
